  "original_title": "\u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b90.\u0b8e\u0bae\u0bcd.\u0b8e\u0baa\u0bcd. \u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "IMF with President negotiation",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Another round of talks between President Ranil Wickremesinghe and representatives of the International Monetary Fund was held yesterday (26) afternoon to find a solution to the current financial crisis in the country.",
        "In this meeting held at the President's Office, President Ranil Wickremesinghe joined the discussion through Zoom technology and positive views were exchanged on both sides.",
        "In today's discussion regarding the Treasury including Electricity Tariff Amendment and Liquor Act, it was agreed to provide the information by next Monday in compliance with the request made by the representatives of the International Monetary Fund to provide the necessary additional information.",
        "International Monetary Fund financial advisers, legal advisers attended yesterday's talks and it was decided to hold the next round of talks next Wednesday (31).",
        "Peter Breuer, Chairman of the International Monetary Fund's Consultative Council, Vice-Chairman Osiro Kosaigo, IMF Permanent Representative to Sri Lanka Tobagans, Chief of Staff to the President and Senior Adviser to the President on National Security Sagala Ratnayake, Secretary to the President Saman Ekanayake, Central Bank Governor Kalanidhi Nandalal Weerasinghe, Senior officials of the Central Bank, including the Treasury Secretary, participated in the discussion. (a)"
      ],
